  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">RowWidth</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For MODFLOW and PHAST models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">RowWidth</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">({Row}) returns the width of the cell or element row specified by its one optional argument Row. For SUTRA models, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">RowWidth</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns zero. If the optional argument is not included, the function uses the row of the node or element for which the formula is being calculated.</text></para>
  </body>
